Last-ditch efforts have been made to the US Supreme Court and Missouri agencies to stay the execution based on the claims of innocence and the presence of exculpatory DNA evidence.

name: NOAA
summary: The National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) is monitoring a tropical disturbance in the Gulf of Mexico and providing updates for the region. NOAA has also released its winter forecast for the United States, predicting a La Niña pattern, which typically brings cooler and wetter conditions to the northern part of the country. The agency has also published specific forecasts for regions such as Massachusetts, where another mild winter is expected. NOAA has debuted imagery from its new GOES-19 satellite, providing enhanced weather monitoring capabilities. Additionally, the agency has launched a first-of-its-kind interagency website dedicated to sea level rise, and its ocean robots are gathering data on deep ocean warming.

name: California banning plastic bags
summary: California has enacted a comprehensive ban on plastic shopping bags at grocery stores, marking a significant step towards reducing plastic waste and protecting the environment. Governor Gavin Newsom signed the legislation into law, effectively prohibiting all single-use plastic bags at grocery store checkouts. This new law builds on previous efforts to curb plastic bag use, which had proven inadequate. The ban will take effect in 2023, providing businesses with ample time to transition to paper or reusable bags. The legislation aims to reduce plastic pollution and encourage sustainable practices, aligning with California's commitment to environmental conservation.

name: Government shutdown
summary: Amidst concerns of a looming government shutdown, Congress has been engaged in a series of negotiations and maneuvers to avoid a lapse in funding. The House of Representatives rejected a temporary funding bill, while Republican leaders announced a three-month spending deal. Representative Mike Johnson announced a vote on a bill to avert the shutdown. The House also voted to reject a GOP bill aimed at preventing a shutdown. Experts advise understanding the complex process by which the US government obtains funding. A new spending deal has been reached, reducing the likelihood of a shutdown. The House Republicans' efforts to pass a spending bill failed, while Representative Mike Johnson is expected to vote on a surrender resolution. Speaker Mike Johnson has proposed a new strategy to avert the shutdown, including additional funding for the Secret Service.

name: Grotesquerie
summary: Travis Kelce, the Pro Bowl tight end, has made his acting debut in the upcoming horror anthology series 'Grotesquerie.' The series creator, Ryan Murphy, specifically wrote the role with Kelce in mind, praising his natural acting abilities. Kelce's performance has received rave reviews, with co-stars and critics alike commending his talent and screen presence. Despite the show's dark and gruesome themes, it is not the first time Kelce has appeared on screen, having previously made cameos in "The Late Show with Stephen Colbert" and "New Girl." His acting coach helped him prepare for months, and his co-stars have expressed their belief that he has a promising future in Hollywood.

name: Young Dolph
summary: The murder trial of Young Dolph is currently underway in Memphis, focusing on the events surrounding the rapper's fatal ambush in 2022. One of the admitted gunmen has testified against Justin Johnson, providing key information. The trial, which began on Monday, has seen the selection of a jury and the presentation of evidence. Suspect Corey Miller has admitted to shooting Young Dolph and cleaning up the vehicle used in the crime. Prosecutors have alleged that Big Jook, an alleged gang leader, offered a $100,000 bounty for Young Dolph's murder. The trial continues, with further updates and testimony expected.

name: Rodri
summary: Manchester City's midfielder, Rodri, has suffered a season-ending knee injury during the Premier League match against Arsenal. This significant setback for the team and manager Pep Guardiola could have major implications for their title hopes. Reports indicate that Rodri has damaged his anterior cruciate ligament (ACL), which will require an extended period of recovery. The injury has raised concerns about Manchester City's ability to maintain their dominance in the league, as they have lost a significant number of matches when Rodri has been absent. Rival teams may seek to capitalize on the team's weakened defense without Rodri's presence on the field.
